    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "The intent of our preparedness and response work is to provide immediate life-saving assistance to disaster affected populations with a special focus on children. Save the Children provides support to affected communities ensure effective preparedness systems are in place to minimize the negative effects of disasters on children and their families. It advocates to influence and support key humanitarian actors (donors, government, I/NGOs, Nepal Red Cross Society) to prioritize children's well-being in an emergency.The project will enhance the emergency preparedness and response capacities of Nepal country office, partners and key local authorities in an event of a mega disaster. By doing so it aims to reduce the vulnerabilities of communities severely affected by disasters through a cost-effective, efficient, timely, appropriate and coordinated humanitarian response in view of established humanitarian standards."
      },
